# Force LF line endings on environment files. A CRLF .env file makes every
# value end in a stray carriage return (e.g. "true\r"), which silently breaks
# boolean flag parsing and credentials (an OPENAI_API_KEY ending in "\r" fails
# auth). Keeping these LF-only avoids that class of bug regardless of the OS
# the file was edited on.
*.env text eol=lf
.env text eol=lf
.env.* text eol=lf
